  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let them adjust to room temperature</p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thick strips</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> lengthways into 2 thick strips per person</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646738553150-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646738553150-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646738553150-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646738553150-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1646738553150-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced pepper</strong> and <strong>courgette strips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) lined with<strong> tin foil</strong></p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until the pepper and courgette are tender and charred</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646738562207-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646738562207-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646738562207-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646738562207-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1646738562207-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized cubes</p><p>Add the <strong>cubed potatoes</strong> to a separate baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25 min or until crispy and golden – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1646738572350-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
